DESCRIPTION:Here’s a link to the March second Saturday ride: https://ridewi
 thgps.com/routes/54187228\n\nThe plan is to go from Davis to Hedgerow Farms
  to see if any of the flower fields are blooming\, ride to the scenic west 
 end of Road 29\, stop in Winters for a snack or lunch at Upper Crust\, and 
 then head back to Davis.\n\nMore details below. Please let me know if you n
 eed additional information.\nThanks\,\n-Anne\, (916) 206-2922\n\nDate: Seco
 nd Saturday – March 14\, 2026\nStart time: 9:00 a.m.\nStart location: Davis
 : Westlake Shopping Center\, 1260 Lake Blvd.\nDistance: 45 miles\nContact: 
 Anne Huber\; anneh@dcn.org\; 916-206-2922\nServices (Food\, water\, bathroo
 ms): in Winters at mile 32\, so you might want to bring a snack\nNo need to
  RSVP\nRain cancellation or postponement: communicated via the listserv.\nP
 ace: 14 - 17 mph with regroups. The speed is meant to be an indicator of sp
 eed on flat terrain with no wind. People can go faster if they want as long
  as they are willing to regroup. There might be some stopping for scenery.\
 nRoute: https://ridewithgps.com/routes/54187228\n\nFor general information 
 about the second Saturday ride and bicycling with the Davis Bike Club\, ple
 ase see: https://davisbikeclub.org/2nd-sat-explorer-ride/\n\nIt includes th
 e following: “Cycling has inherent risks. Any cyclist taking part in a DBC 
 ride releases DBC from any liability. Guests are welcome to ride with DBC f
 or one ride\; for subsequent rides\, you must be a member of the Club. By r
 iding with a DBC group ride you acknowledge that you have read and understa
 nd this. Helmets are required on all rides"
